@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Identifying Divisions & Spans";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <h2>3. Identifying Divisions & Spans</h2>

    <p>Divisions, or <span class="text-danger">&lt;div&gt;</span>, and <span class="text-danger">&lt;span&gt;</span> are HTML elements that act as containers solely for styling purposes.</p>

    <p>As generic containers, they do not come with any overarching meaning or semantic value. Paragraphs are semantic in that content wrapped within a <span class="text-danger">&lt;p&gt;</span> element is known and understood as a paragraph. <span class="text-danger">&lt;div&gt;</span> and <span class="text-danger">&lt;span&gt;</span> do not hold any such meaning and are simply containers.</p>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("SemanticsOverview", "WebDesign")" class="btn btn-outline-primary">← Semantics Overview</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("Elements", "WebDesign")" class="btn btn-primary">HTML Elements →</a>
    </div>
</div>

